    "Motivations.We distinguish between intrinsic and extrinsic motivation.",
    "When individuals are intrinsically motivated, they engage in an activity because they are interested in and enjoy the activity.",
    "When they are extrinsically motivated, they engage in activities for instrumental or other reasons, such as receiving a reward [51].",
    "Most of our participants were primarily intrinsically motivated to attack LLMs and engaged in the activity on their own time.",
